cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with partitioning planar point sets into polygons, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper provides an algorithm to construct such a partition in polynomial time. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper characterizes the problem of partitioning planar point sets into polygons of specified sizes. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the problem of finding a specified 2-factor in the visibility graph of the point set, which is related to graph theory. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper shows that the generalized problem of finding a K_k-factor of the visibility graph of a given point set for k ≥ 5 is NP-hard.
